post_text:
The Piqua Education Foundation is searching for an Executive Director. The primary functions of the Executive Director will be to foster good relations with donors and recipients, to maintain records of donations and grant recipients, and to take the lead in fundraising efforts. In addition, the Executive Director will support the Board of Directors and its committees and actively promote the Foundation within the community.
The Executive Director must be organized, have effective communication skills, and be able to work efficiently and independently. Proficiency in basic software will be required. Fluency in using social media and digital communications would be desirable, as would prior experience in not-for-profit fundraising and donor development.
Anyone interested may send questions or a resume to pef@piqua.org.

"Dear Piqua Community,

My family and I would like to offer our sincere appreciation for all the emotional, physical, and monetary support you have offered to us during this extremely difficult
time.

We have been overwhelmed by the outpouring of kindness from the Piqua community. I'm truly blessed to work for a district that cares so deeply for its employees.

As we try to find a path forward, we are buoyed by the fact that so many are determined to help ease our pain.

With Great Gratitude,
Brian, Marcella, and William Gillespie"

post_text:
We want to celebrate 7 Springcreek Third Graders for their hard work and successful scores in the National Noetic Math Spring 2020 Competition!

There were 2,756 3rd graders across the country who competed and 81 of those kids earned the status of National Honor Roll.

Two of those 81 top students are Springcreek Third Graders!!

Their math teachers are Mrs. Everett & Mrs. Stuchell (GIS). National Honor Roll students will receive a medal in the fall and all students earn a certificate.

We are so proud of their growth & hard work during this time of digital learning!

Connor S - National Honor Roll & National Honorable Mention & Team Leader
Bronson K - National Honor Roll & National Honorable Mention & Team Leader
Addison L- National Honorable Mention
Nolan B - National Honorable Mention
Kaylie P - National Honorable Mention
Savannah G - National Honorable Mention
Tiffany L - Participation

post_text:
In honor of the Class of 2020, Piqua City Schools will light up Alexander Stadium/Purk Field for 20 minutes at 8:20 PM (20:20 Military Time) on April 20/20 to honor our outstanding senior class.

The stadium and lot will remain closed by order of the Governor, but we encourage all Piqua households to turn on your porch lights to help us light up the city in support of these young men and women of our community.

We will release a video along with photos of the stadium lit up. We encourage you to share photos and/or videos with your special message of support on your lit up porch on social media as well.

We are proud of you class of 2020! #wearepiqua

post_text:
Back before school was remote, our Washington students were definitely up for the Right to Read Challenge!

Our goal was 40,000 minutes --- They read 58,162 minutes! Hooray! üôå

We calculated the results by tribe which each consist of a kindergarten, first, second, and third grade class. The results are as follows:
Coyote Tribe - 3040 minutes
Deer Tribe - 5009 minutes
Fox Tribe - 5095 minutes
Bear Tribe - 5,109 minutes
Hawk Tribe - 5,228 minutes

And in 1st place, the Eagle Tribe with 5,600 minutes!

Please keep up these awesome reading and fitness activities! #WeArePiqua
